On August 23, 2019, the President signed two laws into effect. The first, H.R. 1250, designates the United States Postal Service facility in Hardin, Texas as the Lucas Lowe Memorial Post Office. The second, H.R. 3245, known as the "Restore the Harmony Way Bridge Act," transfers ownership of the Harmony Way Bridge from the White County Bridge Commission to the states of Illinois and Indiana.